article.headline: CS Northridge 100, Long Beach St. 61
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Deon Tresvant scored 19 points to lead five Cal State Northridge players in double figures in a 100-61 rout of Long Beach State Saturday. Jayme Miller had 18 points and nine rebounds, Calvin Chitwood scored 14 and freshman Lauren Heard scored 13 as the Matadors (14-4, 6-0) remained unbeaten in the Big West. Josh Jenkins added a career-high 11 assists for Cal State Northridge. Donovan Morris scored 25 and Brice Gallow scored a career-high 17 for Long Beach State (4-14, 1-5). The Matadors held the 49ers without a field goal for the final seven minutes of the first half for a 47-26 halftime lead, and led by as many as 41 in the second half.
